Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getPtnPinStatus(25.10)                                  getPtnPinStatus(25.10)

Name
       getPtnPinStatus  -  Retrieves  the pin status that was defined with the
       setPtnPinStatus command

Syntax
       getPtnPinStatus

       [-help]

       [-cell <cellName>]

       [-pin {<pinName | pinNameList>}]

       Retrieves the pin status that was defined with the setPtnPinStatus com-
       mand.

Parameters
       -cell<cellName>
              Specifies the name of the partition. You can use wildcards  (*?)
              with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each getPtnPinStatus parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getPtnPinStatus.

       -pin<pinName>|<pinNameList>
              Specifies the name of the pin(s) of the partition. You  can  use
              wildcards (*?) with this parameter.

              Default: If the pin name is not specified, the command is run on
              all pins.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command tells the status of pin DATA of partition EUG:

       getPtnPinStatus -pin DATA -cell EUG

Related Information
              * setPtnPinStatus

              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

